There's a sort of weird Scala trick you can use to avoid these two source files. Just to this in the test suite source file:

```
package __root__.test.custom.listener {
  
  class DummyQueryExecutionListener { ...
    
  }
  
}
```

Then the test source is more self-contained, and you can attach the comment about the package name to the package declaration.
